==English==
===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[eln]]'' “unit of measure of 45 inches,” originally “length of the arm,” from Proto-Indo-European ''*el-'' “elbow, forearm”

===Noun===

'''ell'''

1. A [[measure]] for [[cloth]].

2. An extension usually at right angles to one end of a building.

3. Something that is L -shaped.

